ty and moral and political plurality. In The Crooked Timber of Humanity he exposes the links between the ideas of the past and the social and political cataclysms of our own time: between the Platonic belief in absolute truth and the lure of authoritarianism; between the eighteenth-century reactionary ideologue Joseph de Maistre and twentieth-century Fascism; between the romanticism of Schiller and Byron and the militant--and sometimes genocidal--nationalism that convulses the modern world. This new edition features a revised text that supplants all previous versions, a new foreword in which award-winning novelist John Banville discusses Berlin's life and ideas, particularly his defense of pluralism, and a substantial new appendix that provides rich context, including letters by Berlin and previously uncollected writings, most notably his virtuoso review of Bertrand Russell's A History of Western Philosophy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 05. Dez 2022) 0aAufsatzsammlung. 0aCivilisation moderne et contemporaine. 0aCivilization, Modern. 0aIdeengeschichte. 0aPhilosophie. 0aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aAge of Enlightenment.  aAnalogy.  aAtheism.  aAuthoritarianism.  aBertrand Russell.  aBook.  aCalculation.  aCertainty.  aChauvinism.  aCivilisation (TV series).  aClassicism.  aCriticism.  aDespotism.  aDivision of labour.  aDreyfus affair.  aEmpiricism.  aExistentialism.  aExplanation.  aFalsity.  aFanaticism.  aForm of life (philosophy).  aFrederick the Great.  aGiambattista Vico.  aGood and evil.  aHerder.  aHis Family.  aHistoricism.  aHumiliation.  aHumility.  aHypothesis.  aIdealism.  aIdeology.  aImmanuel Kant.  aImperialism.  aIndividualism.  aInstitution.  aIntelligentsia.  aIsaiah Berlin.  aJerusalem Prize.  aJews.  a